</title><link>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/6139/how-to-use-the-default-font-used-by-i3-status-bar-in-the-terminal-emulator/?comment=6167#comment-6167</link><description>I am not sure if there are any packages/distributions configured that way, but i3 does also look in `/etc/xdg/i3/config` (or rather `$XDG_CONFIG_DIRS/i3/config`) for its configuration. Even before it looks for `~/.i3/config` or `/etc/i3/config`. So it may also get its configuration from there.</description><pubDate>Sun, 21 Jun 2015 22:10:04 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/6139/how-to-use-the-default-font-used-by-i3-status-bar-in-the-terminal-emulator/?comment=6167#comment-6167</guid></item><item><title>Comment by Airblader for &lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;grep font /etc/i3/config
