</title><link>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/6139/how-to-use-the-default-font-used-by-i3-status-bar-in-the-terminal-emulator/?comment=6143#comment-6143</link><description>While this should work in most cases without user configuration, it is not fool proof. i3 looks for a configuration in 4 locations, two of them depend on a environment variable. You can use `i3 -C -V` to see which file i3 actually uses.</description><pubDate>Fri, 19 Jun 2015 06:14:38 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/6139/how-to-use-the-default-font-used-by-i3-status-bar-in-the-terminal-emulator/?comment=6143#comment-6143</guid></item></channel></rss>